FuncDef: This command specifies the local priority of the tunnel group. This is used to elect the master (higher number is the master). If priorities are the same, then the peer with the more active ISA becomes the master. If the priority and the number of active ISAs are the same, then the peer with the higher IP address is the master.

ParaDef.Info: Specifies the priority of the tunnel-group. Values-0 to 255.
